added.title: We're Off to Get Awards
added.description: During an awards ceremony, Robin is swept up by a tornado and arrives in a magical land.

added.title: Bat Scouts
added.description: To reach the highest rank in the Bat Scouts, Robin teaches the other Titans important vigilante skills.

added.title: Genie President
added.description: Robin hatches a plan to get rich off pennies, but Starfire believes they are magical.

added.title: Don't Be An Icarus
added.description: Robin tries to tell some Greek myths but the other Titans give their own fractured versions instead.

added.title: The Gold Standard
added.description: It's St. Patrick's Day and after wishing to become a leprechaun, Beast Boy becomes obsessed with gold.

added.title: Classic Titans
added.description: To prove his point about classic superhero cartoons, Control Freak sends the Titans to a former version of Teen Titans Go!

added.title: Career Day
added.description: Robin forces the other Titans to forget their dreams and find regular, boring jobs.

added.title: Demon Prom
added.description: Trigon makes Raven attend her prom and she brings along the other Titans to upset him.

added.title: Beast Boy's St. Patrick's Day Luck, and It's Bad
added.description: The Titans (except Beast Boy) are cursed on St. Patrick's Day and must travel to the end of the rainbow for the cure.

added.title: Gem Glow
added.description: Steven thinks his favorite ice cream sandwiches are the trick to summoning his magic shield but learns otherwise when facing off with an acid-spewing insect monster.

added.title: Laser Light Cannon
added.description: A magical comet hurtles toward Beach City, and Steven must dig through his father's collection of old junk, and the past, to find the weapon that can save the town.

added.title: Cheeseburger Backpack
added.description: A mission to the Lunar Sea Spire takes a treacherous turn, but Steven has packed his totally amazing Cheeseburger Backpack with anything they could ever need!

added.title: The Grades
added.description: Miss Simian discovers a failed test from Gumball's past that brings down his grade point average. This means he has to retake kindergarten all over again, much to her delight. But by demoting him Miss Simian has inadvertently brought herself down, and they're left with no choice but to team up if they want things back to normal.

added.title: The Girlfriend
added.description: Jamie has decided she needs a sweetheart and, unlucky for him, she has decided Darwin is the best candidate.

added.title: The Words
added.description: Darwin is too polite to speak his mind, so Gumball teaches him to be direct via an epic battle of insults.

added.title: The Hero
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are determined to prove to their dad that he is their hero, at any cost!

added.title: The World
added.description: The amazing world of Elmore is full of inanimate objects that aren't nearly as inanimate as you might hope!

added.title: Little Homeschool
added.description: Welcome to Little Homeschool, a place on earth where Gems from all over the universe can come learn how to live together peacefully! But there's one Gem who refuses to attend.

added.title: Guidance
added.description: Amethyst has been helping Little Homeschool Gems find jobs on the boardwalk, but Steven isn't sure about her approach.

added.title: The Grid Car
added.description: Tulip, a headstrong 13-year-old girl, finds a mysterious train where every car contains its own universe.

added.title: The Beach Car
added.description: Tulip strikes a deal with a cat in an attempt to get home, but is the price worth it?

added.title: The Corgi Car
added.description: Tulip and One-One explore a car full of Corgis and face off against a mysterious monster.

added.title: The Crystal Car
added.description: Tulip, Atticus, and One-One enter a crystal forest car and have to take part in a musical ritual.

added.title: The Cat's Car
added.description: Tulip has to face her past.

added.title: The Unfinished Car
added.description: The gang enters an unfinished train car and tries to fix it.

added.title: The Chrome Car
added.description: The gang meets a familiar face in a mirrored car.

added.title: The Ball Pit Car
added.description: The gang is confronted by a strange new force on a Ball Pit Car adventure.

added.title: The Past Car
added.description: Tulip takes a risk trusting an old foe.

added.title: The Engine
added.description: Tulip makes it to the front of the train and is faced with a choice.

added.title: Cleaning Day
added.description: Victor & Valentino gain a newfound respect for cleanliness after Chata's house traps them inside its labyrinth of ancient, magical walls.

added.title: The Babysitter
added.description: Vic & Val want to sneak out to a secret fireworks show but are thwarted when their new babysitter, Xochi, outsmarts them at every turn.

added.title: Hurricane Chata
added.description: When V & V discover that Chata's emotions control the water in the lake, they use it to their advantage and start their own wave pool business.

added.title: Lonely Haunts Club
added.description: Instead of celebrating Valentine's Day, Vic & Val take on a dare to explore a haunted mansion with their rivals, Charlene & Pineapple.

added.title: Suerte
added.description: When Vic cheats on an enchanted board game, the malevolent characters come to life, and it's up to V & V to figure out how to put them back in the game.

added.title: The Dark Room
added.description: After getting rejected by a photography club, Val tries to get a picture of the legendary Chupacabra in order to prove himself.

added.title: The Collector
added.description: When Vic accidentally loses one of Val's prized coins Val makes a deal with a mysterious antiques collector to replace it, but the deal has terrible consequences.

added.title: The Boy Who Cried Lechuza
added.description: After faking an injury to get out of work, Vic gains sympathy from everyone while unknowingly attracting attention from a dangerous mythical creature.

added.title: Boss For a Day
added.description: When Chata lets Vic be the boss of the taco stand for the day Vic decides to fire Val, which has disastrous consequences.

added.title: Cuddle Monster
added.description: After being told by Chata that they can't get a pet, Vic & Val adopt a wild lizard, unaware of its magical properties, and decide to keep it secret from Chata.

added.title: Paint That a Shame
added.description: Leshawna creates a paint balloon fight to decide who gets to come with her to an amusement park.

added.title: Snots Landing
added.description: Beth gets Courtney's diorama furniture stuck up her nose and Courtney needs it back before the diorama contest judge arrives.

added.title: Know it All
added.description: Courtney must go all day without correcting her friends which is hard because they do everything wrong!

added.title: Battle at Biggie Box
added.description: Ben and Billy Billions go head to head over a Sumo Slammer Set sold exclusively inside the world's largest shopping center, only to find six-year-old Simon Sez has gotten it first! A battle royal ensues inside a store that seemingly has everything except an easy to find exit.

added.title: Bon Voyage
added.description: Aboard the SS Pettigrew on its final voyage, Ben must not only battle seasickness but Steam Smythe, who looks to use his mechanical creatures to sink the steamship's modern replacement and the passengers with it!

added.title: Mayhem in Mascot
added.description: After their attempt to get a photo with every storefront mascot is foiled, Ben and Gwen sneak out at night to get their photo with the wooden bear totem known as "Yawk", only to find he and the other mascots have come to life!

added.title: Screamcatcher
added.description: When a cavity forces Ben to the dentist his day gets even worse when the malevolent magician Hex uses a nearby dream catcher to bring our hero's fears to life and transports them both to a nightmarish dreamscape.

added.title: Tooth Trouble
added.description: Puppycorn loses his first tooth and Unikitty's excited for her little bro, now he​ ​gets a visit from​ ​the​ ​legendary Tooth Fairy!​ ​But when the Tooth Fairy is a no-show, Unikitty and her friends take on the mantle and responsibilities. But will they play too fast and loose with loose teeth and hit a raw nerve?

added.title: Roadtrip Ruckus
added.description: Richard has decided to take Unikitty and the gang for a pleasant and relaxing 10 hour road trip. At first everyone is against the trip, but they soon start to have fun. Unfortunately, their idea of fun is not Richard's.  He soon begins to give in to his inner road-rage. To make matters worse they are being chased by a killer semi-truck, and their car has been invaded by weird bug hitchhiker.  Will Richard loose it, or will the trip be a great success?

added.title: Election Day
added.description: In an effort to prove to Master Frown that she is no tyrant, Unikitty agrees to hold an election to see who will be the new princess of the Unikingdom. In a shock, Master Frown takes an early lead in the poles. Unikitty discovers Frown is winning because he's cheating. Will she resort to her own dirty tricks to win the election or stay true to her self and try to win by being nice?

added.title: Camp Unikitty
added.description: The gang's set for an awesome weekend of glamorous, easy-living camping out in fun, friendly nature! But when Hawkodile challenges their idea of camping (it should be a fight for survival in the hostile woods), the gang switch places, with Hawkodile living a luxurious glamp life while Unikitty and the others survive in the wild. Will Unikitty still believe the "great outdoors" are all that great if they meet their doom by natural causes?

added.title: Who Took Toast
added.description: When Toast disappears from Unikitty's party she leads a search to find him and expose the toast-napper.

added.title: Tasty Heist
added.description: Richard's prepared one of the tastiest desserts ever, but he's locked it up tight until the friends have their boring dinner. This will not stand. Unikitty organizes a heist, assembling the friends as a crack team to get in, get out, and eat that tasty snack without Richard knowing. But this heist has hiccups. Can the friends take the cake?

added.title: Beach Daze
added.description: Unikitty and the gang gear up for a fun day at the beach... but when Master Frown shows up as the lifeguard to spoil their plans in the sand, Unikitty and the gang embark on a beach quest to find the legendary Perfect Spot, far away from Frown's tyrannical rule. But can they get there before Frown and claim it for their own or will their quest turn out to be a real beach bummer?

added.title: Tragic Magic
added.description: After Richard puts on an amateur magic show, Dr. Fox becomes obsessed with figuring out how his science-defying tricks are done. But as she sets about using all of her genius intellect finding experimental ways to pull off the little pup's party tricks, will she accidentally ruin the wonder of magic?

added.title: Landlord Lord
added.description: The Land Lord has threatened Master Frown and Brock with eviction unless they fix the damage they've done to their apartment. Worried, Brock invites Unikitty and the gang to help. Instead of doing what the guys want to their place, she proceeds to do what she wants. Realizing her error, she returns the apartment to its former disgusting state, but now Frown and Brock are in danger of eviction again. They must team up with Unikitty and the gang to battle the Land Lord and save their home.

added.title: Space Mission: Danger
added.description: After their spaceship explodes, Unikitty and the gang float helplessly through space. As they try to formulate a plan that will get them home safe, they flash back to how each of them is responsible for their ship being destroyed. Will they make it home, and more importantly who will be to blame if they don't.

added.title: Return of the Honeysuckle Rangers
added.description: Craig discovers that the Honeysuckle Rangers have snuck into his side of the Creek to steal his most prized possession.

added.title: Kelsey the Elder
added.description: A spat between the Elders of the Creek leaves an opening in their tabletop role playing game, so Kelsey joins the campaign!

added.title: The Climb
added.description: Craig's phone gets stuck in Mt. Sycamore, the tallest tree in the creek!

added.title: Big Pinchy
added.description: JP leads his friends on a voyage to find the biggest crayfish in the creek.

added.title: The Kid From 3030
added.description: The kids meet a mysterious kid from the future and try to help him complete his mission.

added.title: Power Punchers
added.description: Fed up with losing in video games to his Dad, Craig seeks training in the Creek.

added.title: Creek Cart Racers
added.description: A high-speed race with a high-stakes prize may be too much for Craig and his friends.

added.title: Secret Book Club
added.description: Kelsey starts a super secret book club to introduce Craig and JP to the joys of reading.

added.title: Dia de limpieza
added.description: Victor y Valentino adquieren un nuevo respeto por la limpieza después de que la casa de Chata los atrapa dentro de su laberinto de paredes antiguas y mágicas.

added.title: La ninera
added.description: Vic y Val quieren colarse en un espectáculo secreto de fuegos artificiales, pero su plan se ve frustrado cuando su nueva niñera, Xochi, los supera en todo momento.

added.title: Huracan Chata
added.description: Cuando V y V descubren que las emociones de Chata controlan el agua del lago, deciden sacar ventaja y comienzan su propio negocio de piscinas de olas.

added.title: Loteria
added.description: Cuando Vic hace trampa en un juego de mesa encantado, los malvados personajes cobran vida, y V y V son los responsables de averiguar cómo volver a ponerlos en el juego.

added.title: El club de los solitarios
added.description: En lugar de celebrar el Día de San Valentín, Vic y Val se atreven a explorar una mansión encantada con sus rivales, Charlene y Piña.

added.title: El cuarto oscuro
added.description: Tras ser rechazado por un club de fotografía, Val intenta conseguir una foto del legendario Chupacabra para demostrar su valor.

added.title: El Coleccionista
added.description: Cuando, por accidente, Vic pierde una de las preciadas monedas de Val, Val hace un trato con un misterioso coleccionista de antigüedades para reemplazarla, pero el trato tiene consecuencias terribles.

added.title: Victor y la Lechuza
added.description: Después de fingir una lesión para no tener que trabajar, Vic se gana la compasión de todos mientras que, sin saberlo, atrae la atención de una peligrosa criatura mítica.

added.title: Jefe por un dia
added.description: Cuando Chata deja que Vic sea el jefe del puesto de tacos por un día, él decide despedir a Val, lo que trae consecuencias desastrosas.

added.title: Nueva Mascota
added.description: Después de que Chata les dijera que no pueden tener una mascota, Vic y Val adoptan un lagarto salvaje, sin conocer sus propiedades mágicas, y deciden mantenerlo en secreto para que Chata no se entere.

added.title: Mystery Sleepover
added.description: KO, Enid and Rad attempt to solve a mystery.

added.title: Crossover Nexus
added.description: When KO finds himself trapped inside an mysterious place, he encounters other Cartoon Network Heroes and they band together to escape.

added.title: Presenting Joe Cuppa
added.description: KO tries to help his favorite comedian, Joe Cuppa.

added.title: Legends of Mr. Gar
added.description: Rad and Enid reminisce about when they started working at the bodega and learned how amazing Mr. Gar really is.

added.title: We're Captured
added.description: Boxman captures KO, Enid and Rad, but seems a little distracted.

added.title: Oscar & Hedgehog's Melody
added.description: Susie holds the annual talent show that has the rest of the campers competing to win.

added.title: Feeling Spacey
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog arrive on a planet that has no emotions.

added.title: Ghost the Boy
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog befriend a ghost who can't remember who he is.

added.title: Computer Vampire
added.description: Oscar finds a mysterious old video game in the library.

added.title: The Basketball Liaries
added.description: With the help from Basketball, Oscar makes an impressive shot that scores him a spot on the Gold League.

added.title: Popular Banana Split
added.description: Hedgehog and Max discover a tiny high school when they are accidentally shrunk by a science experiment.

added.title: Time Traveling Quick Pants
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog learn about a quicksand that lets them go back in time.

added.title: It's My Party
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog plan a surprise birthday party for Susie.

added.title: Moon Problems
added.description: The Moon gets sad when Oscar loses his friendship bracelet.

added.title: Monster Visit
added.description: The monsters get nervous when their Godmonster comes for a visit.

added.title: The Wild Hunt
added.description: A fierce creature is terrorizing the Candy Kingdom but before Finn can slay the beast, he must first overcome a guilty conscience.

added.title: Lost and Found
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby go get a wallet.

added.title: Kill' Em with Kindness
added.description: Pops wants to be friends with someone.

added.title: The Thin Yellow Line
added.description: Finn and Jake infiltrate the Banana Guard ranks and stumble upon a conspiracy.

added.title: Lame Lockdown
added.description: The head scientist puts Mordecai and Rigby on a 24-hour lockdown inside the Dome, but they want to sneak out and see one of their favorite bands.

added.title: The Tower
added.description: Finn doesn't like any of the new arms the princesses give him, so he builds a tower into space to find his dad and get his old arm back.

added.title: Lift With Your Back
added.description: Rigby wants to prove to Mordecai that he can earn a paycheck from another job.

added.title: The Visitor
added.description: A vision leads Finn to a friendly civilization and a mysterious crash site.

added.title: Pizza Steve's Past
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang learn of Pizza Steve's past stint in the food service industry. Pizza Steve wasn't always the Pizza Steve they know and love.

added.title: What's the Big Idea?
added.description: Pizza Steve and Mr. Gus try to help Uncle Grandpa get an idea.

added.title: The Vault
added.description: When Finn starts sleepwalking and dreaming about the Green Lady he filed away in his memory vault, Jake and BMO help him tap into his repressed memories to uncover a secret past. Who is the Green Lady? And how is she connected to Finn?

added.title: Don't Drink the Water
added.description: In Florida, Ben and Max accidentally come in contact with water from The Fountain of Youth. As a result, Max transforms into a kid and Ben a toddler, with Gwen having to deal with both of them. Our trio then must track down Hex who's found the source of the fountain and prevent him from drinking the water that will make him immortal and unstoppable.

added.title: You Can't Handle the Tooth
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and Mr. Gus must rescue Pizza Steve from the Tooth Fairy.

added.title: Disappearing Act
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a young wannabe magician by teaching her a new trick.

added.title: Titanes Clasicos
added.description: Para demostrar su punto de vista sobre los dibujos animados clásicos de superhéroes, iControl Freak envía a los Titanes a una versión antigua de Jóvenes Titanes en Acción!

added.title: Dia de los Trabajos
added.description: Robin obliga a los demás Titanes a olvidar sus sueños y a conseguir trabajos normales y aburridos.

added.title: Baile Demoniaco
added.description: Trigon invita a Raven a su baile de graduación, y ella lleva a los demás Titanes para molestarlo.

added.title: Worm Bin
added.description: After his mom gets a worm bin, Jeff deals with the gross reality that he has a tub of bugs living in his kitchen, and Clarence obsesses over feeding the worms.

added.title: A Change of Face
added.description: In Salem Massachusetts, Ben, Gwen and Max once again go up against Charmcaster, whose goal is to switch souls with Ben and possess the Omnitrix. However, Charmcaster first accidentally switches identities with Gwen, and then as spells fly back and forth, Ben and Gwen even end up in one another's bodies before they team up to get rid of Charmcaster once and for all.

added.title: Birthday
added.description: Jeff and Sumo expect no one to show at Clarence's birthday party, just like last year. When dozens of kids arrive, the boys struggle to get face time with Clarence, the popular party host.

added.title: Capture the Flag
added.description: Water balloon fights, warring factions and the risk of jail time, everything is on the line when Clarence and friends play the biggest game of capture the flag yet! Everyone wants to take home the crown, and the power to control the neighborhood's juice boxes.

added.title: Fishing Trip
added.description: Mel learns that Chad has never taken Clarence fishing, a tradition he sees as a rite of passage, and decides to remedy this with a bonding trip for all the boys! Split into two groups, Mel and Clarence learn a bit about each other while Chad struggles with the ins and outs of fishing.

added.title: Motel
added.description: Following an insect mishap Clarence's house needs to be fumigated forcing Mary, Chad, and Clarence into a motel. In the meantime, Clarence and Chad learn a bit about responsibility while Mary contemplates a life of letting go.

added.title: Messy Bessy
added.description: Seth must clean his room and learn to be a neater person in order to keep Messy Bessy from making his life a nightmare.

added.title: Gut Model
added.description: Muscle Man becomes a model.

added.title: Dulce Acido
added.description: Craig se embarca en un alucinante viaje mientras trata de comer la golosina más ácida del Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Fuerte Williams
added.description: iCuando Craig no puede ir al Arroyo, él y su madre deciden construir el fuerte de cobijas más grande del mundo!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Ghostfreaked Out
added.description: Ben's internal demons get externalized when Ghostfreak escapes from his watch and becomes a full fledged being on his own. The renegade alien then realizes he needs to meld with Ben's DNA in order to survive.

added.title: Spider Sense
added.description: When a monster ruins their relaxing vacation, the Girls run into a familiar face.

added.title: Phantasm Chasm
added.description: After getting sucked into Jared's favorite board game, Buttercup is forced to team-up with him in order to save her sisters.

added.title: Nexo Creativo
added.description: Cuando KO queda atrapado dentro de un lugar misterioso, se encuentra con otros héroes de Cartoon Network y todos se unen para escapar.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Pijamada Misteriosa
added.description: KO, Enid y Rad intentan resolver un misterio.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: El vagon inacabado
added.description: El grupo entra a un vagón sin terminar e intenta arreglarlo.

added.title: El vagon cromado
added.description: El grupo se encuentra con una cara familiar en un vagón espejado.

added.title: El vagon de la piscina de pelotas
added.description: El grupo es confrontado por una nueva y extraña fuerza en una aventura por un vagón lleno de pelotas.

added.title: El vagon del pasado
added.description: Tulip se arriesga al confiar en un viejo enemigo.

added.title: La locomotora
added.description: Tulip logra llegar al frente del tren y debe afrontar una decisión.

added.title: Of Predators and Prey Part 2
added.description: While trapped in Khyber's ship, Ben learns details about the origin of the Nemetrix, and the link between Khyber, Malware, and Dr. Psychobos! (Introducing new Nemetrix alien Tyrannopede.)

added.title: El Popular Banana Split
added.description: Erizo y Max descubren una escuela diminuta cuando, por accidente, un experimento científico los encoge.

added.title: Home on the Run/Top Slot
added.description: Home on the Run: We are introduced to Shun's mysterious backstory, his relationship with his industrialist father and desire for a closer knit family./Top Slot: Dan and Shun butt heads on how best to make the AO a real team amidst growing threats including the mysterious Shargo Ronin.

added.title: Outbreak
added.description: When Dr. Psychobos steals a part out of the Omnitrix, causing chaotic side effects, it's up to Ben, Rook, and a small team of Plumbers get everything back to normal. (Introducing new Ben alien Kickin' Hawk, temp Ben alien Walkatrout, Upchuck Rook.)

added.title: Pantalones Movedizos del Tiempo
added.description: Oscar y Erizo se enteran de la existencia de unas arenas movedizas que les permiten viajar en el tiempo.

added.title: Fathers and Friends/Midsummer Nightmare
added.description: Midsummer Nightmare: Drago and the other AO Bakugan face an unseen threat with earth shattering power only to be left wondering if it was all a dream./Father's and Fiends: Osamu Kazami comes to take his son Shun back home and finds a defiance he hadn't counted on.

added.title: Es mi Fiesta
added.description: Oscar y Erizo planean una fiesta de cumpleaños sorpresa para Susie.

added.title: Dawn Before Dusk
added.description: Dawn Before Dusk, Part 1: The AO meet Benton Dusk discovering that their quiet little corner of the world is about to become much, much larger./Dawn Before Dusk, Part 2: Benton Dusk reveals that the AO have been indentified as persons of interest by powerful corporations including Philomena Dusk's AAAnimus.

added.title: Presentando a Joe Kaffi
added.description: K.O. intenta ayudar a Joe Kaffi, su comediante favorito.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Problemas Lunares
added.description: La Luna se entristece cuando Oscar pierde su brazalete de la amistad.

added.title: Stratified/Maze Daze
added.description: Stratified: The AO embark on a mission into the mysterious labyrinth world of Vestroia to find Strata the Hunter and free the Bakugan he has imprisoned./Maze Daze: Lost in the maze of Vestroia the AO encounter powerful forces that seem to be struggling for control over the alien landscape.

added.title: Visita Monstruosa
added.description: Los monstruos se ponen nerviosos cuando su Dios monstruo llega de visita.

added.title: All Jungled Up/Outer Demons
added.description: All Jungled Up: Still lost in Vestroia the AO experience mind altering effects of the nearby Core Cell and come face to face with the Bakuzon monster Tiko./Outer Demons: The AO find the doorway out of Vestroia only to learn they have entered a mirror world of their own imagining created by the Core Cell.

added.title: Leyendas del Senor Gar
added.description: Rad y Enid recuerdan la época en la que comenzaron a trabajar en el almacén y entendieron lo fabuloso que es el Sr. Gar.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Nos Capturaron
added.description: Box-man captura a K.O., Enid y Rad, pero parece un poco distraído.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Huyendo de casa
added.description: Descubriremos el misterioso pasado de Shun, su relación con su padre (un magnate de la industria), y su deseo por tener una familia más unida.

added.title: Un verdadero lider
added.description: Entre diversas amenazas, como el misterioso Shargo Ronin, Dan y Shun no pueden acordar la mejor forma de convertir a Los Fantásticos en un verdadero equipo.

added.title: Pesadilla de verano
added.description: Drago y los otros Bakugan de Los Fantásticos se enfrentan a una nueva y poderosa amenaza, solo para dejarlos preguntándose si todo habrá sido un sueño.

added.title: Padres y amigos
added.description: Osamu Kazami viene para llevarse a su hijo Shun a casa y se encuentra con un obstáculo que no había contemplado.

added.title: Industrias Dusk Parte 1
added.description: Los Fantásticos conocen a Benton Dusk y descubren que su pequeño mundo está a punto de volverse mucho más grande.

added.title: Industrias Dusk Parte 2
added.description: Benton Dusk revela que Los Fantásticos son considerados personas de interés por poderosas corporaciones como AAAnimus.

added.title: In the Garden of Good and Eddie
added.description: When the girls try a quick-fix on their neglected veggie garden, they are left with a giant, mooching tomato worm they must care for.

added.title: Punos Fuertes
added.description: Harto de perder cuando juega a los videojuegos contra su padre, Craig busca entrenarse en el Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Stratificados
added.description: Los Fantásticos emprenden una misión en el misterioso mundo laberíntico de Vestroia para buscar a Strata El Cazador y liberar a los Bakugan que tiene presos.

added.title: Carrera en el Arroyo
added.description: Una carrera de alta velocidad con un premio de alto riesgo puede ser demasiado para Craig y sus amigos.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Aventura en el laberinto
added.description: Perdidos en el laberinto de Vestroia, Los Fantásticos se enfrentan a poderosas fuerzas que parecen luchar por el control del planeta.

added.title: The Big Sleep
added.description: When the Professor's latest invention wreaks havoc in the house, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls to stop it before it escapes.

added.title: Atrapados en la jungla
added.description: Aún perdidos en Vestroia, Los Fantásticos experimentan los efectos de la Célula Núcleo que altera sus cuerpos, y se encuentran cara a cara con el monstruo Bakugan, Tiko.

added.title: Club de Lectura Secreto
added.description: Kelsey crea un club de lectura supersecreto para introducir a Craig y JP en las alegrías de la lectura.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Demonios internos
added.description: Los Fantásticos encuentran la forma de salir de Vestroia, pero descubren que en realidad están en un mundo paralelo.

added.title: License to Drill
added.description: Mega Man teams up with Bert Wily to take down Drill Man, whose plan to construct hundreds of drill shaped high rises has put Silicon City in both aesthetic and physical danger!

added.title: Rainy Day
added.description: The girls get into trouble when left to entertain themselves on a rainy day.

added.title: All Good in the Wood
added.description: When Suna and Ashley's science project turns into a hungry blob monster, Mega Man must team up with Wood Man to shut down the experiment gone wrong before it devours the city!

added.title: O Mother, Where Art Thou?
added.description: Ma Vreedle threatens to blow up the sun if Ben and the Plumbers don't find her missing son!

added.title: Fire Man in the Hole
added.description: While hiking on a dormant volcano, Aki sets out to retrieve Ashley's lost camera and, as Mega Man, to stop Fire Man from setting off an eruption!

added.title: A Split End
added.description: After replicating Cut Man's powers, Mega Man goes on a perfectionist spree, putting him on a collision course with Cut Man himself, whose latest stint as a hairdresser hasn't helped him overcome his own compulsions.

added.title: All Play and No Work
added.description: Mega Man must resist the influence of a prankster bot named Chaotique, whose devil may care ideology appeals to the overworked superhero, until his friends pay the price for his dalliances.

added.title: Rad Monster Party
added.description: Ben and Rook enlist the help of intergalactic smuggler Rad Dudesman to fly them through the Anur System—the home of the monstrous aliens!

added.title: Rook Tales
added.description: Rook's former teacher will preserve Revonnahgander traditions at any cost.

added.title: Dog Daze/In Focus
added.description: Dog Daze: Lightning discovers a new Bakugan, Artulean, leading to an unhealthy rivalry with Howlkor./In Focus: While Lia's newswoman mom does an expose on the AO Strata the Hunter tries to capture Hydorous.

added.title: The Exit/The Lost and the Cost
added.description: The Exit: The AO compete with a rival Brawling team for ViewTube hits leading to a "winner take all" brawl./The Lost and the Cost: Everett Ray, a promotor, tries to get the AO to join an official league for Bakugan Battling.

added.title: Mr. Moon/What's Wrong with Dan
added.description: Mr. Moon: Wynton finds a new Bakugan who proves difficult to control but things get more complicated when Col. Tripp seizes control of Trox./What's Wrong with Dan: With "Dan" behaving strangely toward the AO Lightning sniffs out the truth- an impostor!

added.title: Babysitting Bedlam/Rubbed the Wrong Way
added.description: Rubbed the Wrong Way: After a Bakugan field errupts the town kids stampede to get their own Bakugan but when the field is contaminated Lia must save the day./Babysitting Bedlam: Dan and Wynton meet a strange boy who leads them into an underground maze where they discover the boy's Bakugan has been enslaved.

added.title: Mask of Power/Story Holes
added.description:
Mask of Power: Philomena Dusk from AAAnimus Corp. hires Magnus and gives him a control implant to bolster the power of his Bakugan to defeat Dan./Story Holes:  
A cryptic call leads the AO in search of a missing Bakugan but they soon realize the call was actually a test from a mysterious benefactor.

added.title: A Guilded Cage
added.description: Mega Man must stop Namagem and an army of hypnotized Good Guild bots from breaking into Dr. Light's lab.

added.title: To Air Is Robot
added.description: Air Man stakes a claim on the skies above Silicon City, threatening anything that trespasses on his airspace.

added.title: Watt's Happening?!
added.description: When Elec Man derails the school play by hijacking Silicon Central's power, Aki/Mega Man must use what he has learned onstage to defeat his supercharged foe.

added.title: Chill Out, Bruh
added.description: Aki and Suna take a rehabilitated Ice Man out for a day in the city, but things take a turn for the worse as he misinterprets their cues and turns a game of hover hockey into a literal freeze out!

added.title: Big Bad Dreams
added.description: When Namagem starts using his Hypno powers to haunt Aki's dreams, our hero must face his fears in the dreamscape.

added.title: El Regreso de los Guardabosques Madreselva
added.description: Craig descubre que los Guardabosques Madreselva se han infiltrado en su lado del Arroyo para robar su posesión más preciada.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Kelsey la Anciana
added.description: Una discusión entre los Ancianos del Arroyo deja un lugar vacante en su juego de rol de mesa, así que Kelsey se une a la campaña.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La Melancolia de Oscar y Erizo
added.description: Susie organiza el concurso anual de talentos, y todos los campistas compiten para ganar.

added.title: Sintiendose Especiales
added.description: Oscar y Erizo llegan a una planeta que no tiene emociones.

added.title: Fantasma, El Nino
added.description: Oscar y Erizo se hacen amigos de un fantasma que no recuerda quién es.

added.title: Vampiro de Computadora
added.description: Oscar encuentra un videojuego viejo y misterioso en la biblioteca.

added.title: Cronicas de Mentiras Basquetboleras
added.description: Con la ayuda de Basketball, Oscar hace un tiro impresionante que le permite conseguir un lugar en la Liga Dorada.

added.title: Enredos perrunos
added.description: Lightning descubre un nuevo Bakugan, Artulean, y eso desata una fuerte rivalidad entre él y Howlkor.

added.title: Bajo los reflectores
added.description: Cuando la reportera Verónica Venegas, madre de Lia, hace un reportaje acerca de Los Fantásticos, Strata El Cazador intenta capturar a Hydorous.

added.title: El equipo Exit
added.description: Los Fantásticos compiten por el número de visitas en sus videos con un equipo rival llamado "El equipo Exit" en una batalla donde se juegan el todo por el todo.

added.title: Perdidas y ganancias
added.description: Un promotor llamado Everett Ray quiere convencer a Los Fantásticos de ingresar a una liga oficial de Batallas Bakugan.

added.title: Sr. Luna
added.description: Wynton encuentra un nuevo Bakugan que resulta difícil de controlar, y las cosas se complican cuando el Coronel Tripp se apodera de Trox.

added.title: Que ocurre con Dan
added.description: Cuando Dan se comporta de forma extraña con los Fantásticos, Lightning olfatea la verdad: iUn impostor!

added.title: Una necesidad inquietante
added.description: La aparición de un nuevo campo Bakugan hace que los chicos del pueblo corran a buscar a sus propios Bakugan. Pero cuando el campo es contaminado, Lia debe salvarlos a todos.

added.title: Tutores Bakugan
added.description: Dan y Wynton conocen a un extraño chico que los lleva a un laberinto subterráneo, donde descubren que el Bakugan del chico ha sido esclavizado.

added.title: Mascara de poder
added.description: Philomena Dusk, de la Corporación AAAnimus, contrata a Magnus y le implanta un dispositivo que aumenta el poder de su Bakugan para derrotar a Dan.

added.title: Una verdad a medias
added.description: Un críptico correo electrónico lleva a Los Fantásticos en busca de un Bakugan desaparecido, pero pronto se dan cuenta de que el correo era una prueba de un misterioso benefactor.

added.title: A escalar
added.description: iEl teléfono de Craig se atasca en el Monte Sicomoro, el árbol más alto del Arroyo!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Don Pellizco
added.description: JP lleva a sus amigos de viaje para encontrar el cangrejo de río más grande del Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El chico del 3030
added.description: Los niños conocen a un misterioso niño del futuro y tratan de ayudarlo a completar su misión.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: The Lepre Con
added.description: On a St. Patrick's Day trip to Ireland, Uncle Grandpa and the gang cross paths with a sneaky leprechaun.

removed.title: El vagon de la playa
removed.description: Tulip cierra un trato con una gata en un intento por volver a casa. ¿Acaso el precio vale la pena?

removed.title: El vagon de cristal
removed.description: Tulip, Atticus y Uno-Uno entran a un vagón con un bosque de cristal y deben participar en un ritual musical.

removed.title: El vagon de los Corgi
removed.description: Tulip y Uno-Uno exploran un vagón lleno de Corgis y se enfrentan a un misterioso monstruo.

removed.title: El vagon cuadriculado
removed.description: Tulip, una obstinada niña de 13 años, encuentra un misterioso tren donde cada vagón contiene su propio universo.

removed.title: Steven's Birthday
removed.description: Steven has a birthday party out at the barn, and decides he has some growing up to do.

removed.title: Message Received
removed.description: Steven has doubts about believing in everyone.

removed.title: It Could've Been Great
